## Context

- keap1-nrf2-pancancer-dependency-atlas: Implemented Phase 4 (PRISM drug sensitivity)
- Phase 4a (task 1305): Genome-wide PRISM screen of 6790 compounds (38 altered vs 590 WT in PRISM)
  - 0 sensitizing hits at FDR<0.1 — broad drug resistance in KEAP1/NRF2-altered
  - 4 resistance hits: S63845 (MCL-1i), walrycin-B, BRD-K06426971, BRD-K68379918
  - Top sub-threshold sensitizers: trimetrexate (d=-0.66), GSK3117391 (d=-0.69)
- Phase 4b (task 1306): Targeted analysis
  - BAY-2402234 (DHODH inhibitor): d=-0.24 pan-cancer, d=-0.31 Lung — trend not significant
  - ATR inhibitor 2: null pan-cancer; resistance in Bladder (d=1.48, FDR=0.002)
  - KL-subtype: 6 lines in PRISM, underpowered
  - UGDH: NOT a gained CRISPR dependency (d=-0.01 pan-cancer)
  - NRF2 activity-UXS1 correlation: r=-0.445 (p=0.003) in altered lines — strongest UXS1 evidence
- Most clinical ATR/CHK1 inhibitors absent from PRISM (ceralasertib, berzosertib, prexasertib)
- Next: analyst to interpret Phase 4 results; no further developer tasks currently queued
